5. AWS Vertical Scaling

TOPIC: AWS: Vertical Scaling - Hands-on Steps
Objective:
Demonstrate vertical scaling (increasing EC2 instance size/resources) by resizing
an existing EC2 instance.
All steps are done using AWS Free Tier eligible instances. Choose only t2.micro or
t3.micro instances.
SECTION 1: Launch a FREE TIER EC2 Instance (cst-R9ST-WebServer)
1. Login to AWS Console → Select N. Virginia (us-east-1) or any Free Tier region.
2. Go to EC2 Dashboard → Click on Instances → Click Launch Instances.
3. Name your instance as cst-R9ST-WebServer-Red9SysTech
4. Choose Amazon Machine Image: Select Amazon Linux 2023 (x86_64) (Free
5. Choose Instance Type: Select t2.micro (Free Tier).

6. Key pair: Create new key pair named cst-R9ST-KeyPair-Red9SysTech → Download
.pem file.

7. Network Settings:

• Create new Security Group named cst-R9ST-SG-Red9SysTech.

• Allow SSH (port 22) from My IP.

• Allow HTTP (port 80) from Anywhere (0.0.0.0/0).

8. Configure storage: Leave default 8 GiB (Free Tier eligible).

9. Click Launch Instance.
10. Wait for status check → Click the instance → Copy public IPv4 address.
SECTION 2: Connect to EC2 & Install Apache (Red9SysTech Touch)
1. Open your terminal.
